                                    Call for Workshop Proposals=0A=
                                                   LICS 2017=0A=
                                 32nd Annual ACM/IEEE Symposium=0A=
                                     on Logic in Computer Science=0A=
=0A=
                                      http://lics.rwth-aachen.de/lics17/=0A=
=0A=
=0A=
The thirty-second Annual ACM/IEEE Symposium on Logic In Computer Science (L=
ICS'17) will be held in Reykjavik, Iceland on June 20=9623, 2017. The works=
hops will take place on June 18=9619, 2017. June 18 will only be used by tw=
o-days workshops (if any), or in case the number of workshops is really lar=
ge. This year, workshop fees should be around 65 euros for a one-day worksh=
op (including lunch and two coffee breaks).=0A=
=0A=
Researchers and practitioners are invited to submit proposals for workshops=
  on topics relating logic =96 broadly construed =96 to computer science or =
related fields. Typically, LICS workshops feature a number of invited speak=
ers and a number of contributed presentations. LICS workshops do not usuall=
y produce formal proceedings. However, in the past there have been special =
issues of journals based in part on certain LICS workshops.=0A=
=0A=
Proposals should include:=0A=
=0A=
         =95 -  A short scientific summary and justification of the proposed=
  topic.=0A=
             This should include a discussion of the particular benefits of =
the topic to the LICS community.=0A=
         =95 -  A discussion of the proposed format and agenda.=0A=
         =95 -  The proposed duration, which is typically one day (two-day w=
orkshops can be accommodated too).=0A=
         =95 -  Procedures for selecting participants and papers.=0A=
         =95 -  Expected number of participants. This is important for the r=
oom!=0A=
         =95 -  Potential invited speakers.=0A=
         =95 -  Plans for dissemination (for example, special issues of jour=
nals).=0A=
=0A=
Proposals should be sent to Patricia Bouyer: bouyer@lsv.fr=0A=
=0A=
** Important Dates **=0A=
=0A=
         Submission deadline:    November 1, 2016=0A=
         Notification:                   November 15, 2016=0A=
         Program of the workshops ready: May 19, 2017=0A=
         Workshops:                      June 18=9619, 2017=0A=
         LICS conference:                June 20=9623, 2017=0A=
=0A=
The workshops selection committee consists of the LICS General Chair, LICS =
Workshops Chair, LICS 2017 PC Chair and LICS 2017 Conference Chair.=0A=


